<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 13 at 12:51AM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Talladega, southwestern Calhoun, northeastern Jefferson and central
St. Clair Counties through 145 AM CDT...
At 1250 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clay, or near Springville, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Anniston, Oxford, Trussville, Pell City, Moody, Springville,
Odenville, Cobb Town, West End-Cobb Town, Saks, Center Point, Clay,
Pinson, Lincoln, Margaret, Argo, Riverside, Ragland, Ohatchee and
Hobson City.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
